HEADWORD: Lock stitch
<hw>Lock" stitch`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A peculiar sort
of stitch formed by the locking of two threads together, as in the work
done by some sewing machines. See <er>Stitch</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

